        "id": "B2D5A34B-5108-43B1-963D-9CC05E035607",
        "title": "Alcatraz Island",
        "description": "Alcatraz Island, the site of pre-Civil War-era fortifications, was the nation’s first military prison, which later became the most notorious maximum security penitentiary in the United States. On November 9, 1969, American Indian people once again came to Alcatraz Island when Richard Oakes, a Mohawk Indian, and a group of Native American supporters set out in a chartered boat to symbolically claim the island for the native people.",
