        "title": "Alcatraz New Industries Building",
        "description": "Alcatraz put the men incarcerated on the island to work manufacturing all sorts of things in the New Industry Building. Constructed in 1939, the complex held a clothing factory, laundry, furniture plants, as well as a brush factory. Men washed army uniforms, made gloves, wove mats, and constructed furniture.",
