        "id": "74F34A35-4FBD-45A2-9D51-E4C4DAD5B906",
        "title": "Lower Prison Complex: Prisoners at Work",
        "description": "Look back down the road and imagine a complex of wooden structures running from here to the Sallyport. These buildings formed the Lower Prison complex, constructed in 1867. Up to 150 men were held here in 150 small cells. The complex also had workshops for making hats and boots, a blacksmith shop, a school for military prisoners, and a mess hall. Most soldiers detained here had committed crimes or broken army regulations.",
