        "id": "FB82E0D1-D736-4787-9F6D-8F85BFC9DDB7",
        "title": "Model Industries Building: Prisoners at Work",
        "description": "The army built the Model Industries Building in 1922 to retrain imprisoned soldiers at the U.S. Disciplinary Barracks. The structure contained a blacksmith shop, plumbing shop, a vocational training school, other workshops, and a band practice room. While some continued to break rocks under heavy guard, others engaged in tending the gardens on the Rock's barren landscape, a form of horticultural therapy.",
        "tags": [
          "Prisoners at Work Tour"
        ],
